==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[archepiscopus]]''', from Greek '''[[archepiskopos]]''', from '''[[arche]]''' ([[αρχι]]) ''first'' or ''chief'' + '''[[episkopos]]''' ([[επισκοπος]]) , ''overseer'' or ''supervisor''

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ɑrʧbɪʃəp/}} ''(US)''
*[[w:SAMPA chart for English|SAMPA]]: /ArtSbIsh@p/ ''(US)''

===Noun===
'''archbishop'''  (''plural:'' '''[[archbishops]]''')
# In the [[Roman Catholic Church]] and other churches, a senior [[bishop]] who is in charge of an [[archdiocese]], and presides over a group of [[diocese]]s called a '''[[province]]'''.

